  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators aimed to investigate TGFB1 and LAMA1 gene polymorphisms in children with
      high myopia in order to determine the genetic basis of large myopic shifts causing severe
      visual impairment and complications.

      Seventy-four children with high myopia (≥6 diopters [D]; study group) and 77 emmetropic
      children (±0.5D; control group) were included. Genetic and polymorphism analyses were
      performed in the Medical Genetics Laboratory using DNA purified from the patients' blood
      samples.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
